def main():
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
        prog="skillgenie",
        description=(
            "Skill manager for the skill-genie repo.\n\n"
            "List, read, validate, install, and update the AI agent skills that\n"
            "live in ./skills/. Skills are distributed to per-runtime directories\n"
            "(~/.claude/skills/, ~/.config/devin/skills/, ~/.agents/skills/, ...)\n"
            "so every supported agent (Claude Code, Devin, Codex, Kiro, OpenClaw,\n"
            "Hermes, OpenCode, Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf, Antigravity) picks them up.\n\n"
            "Run 'skillgenie <command> -h' for per-command details."
        ),
        formatter_class=argparse.RawDescriptionHelpFormatter,
        epilog="""
commands:
  list        List every skill folder in ./skills/ with its description.
  read        Print a skill's full SKILL.md (from repo or ~/.agents/skills/).
  status      Show an install matrix: which runtime has which skill installed.
  validate    Check SKILL.md frontmatter for cross-agent compatibility.
              Run this before committing skill changes.
  install     Copy/symlink a skill into one or more runtime skill directories.
              With no target flag, auto-detects runtimes present on this machine.
  update      Re-install a skill (same as install, but signals a refresh of an
              already-installed skill). Use after editing ./skills/<name>/ or
              pulling upstream changes.
  sync        Clone/pull every remote repo in skills.yaml and install the
              picked skills into ~/.agents/skills/ (and, with --global, into
              every detected native runtime dir). Entries with a 'local:'
              path use your existing checkout directly (no clone, no pull).
              Use after editing skills.yaml or to refresh third-party skills.

target flags (install / update / sync):
  --global / -g      All supported runtimes (overrides auto-detect).
  (no flag)          Auto-detect: every runtime found on this machine.
  --agents           AgentSkills root        (~/.agents/skills/)
  --claude / -cc     Claude Code             (~/.claude/skills/)
  --openclaw / -oc   OpenClaw                (~/.openclaw/skills/)   [copy]
  --hermes           Hermes                  (~/.hermes/skills/)     [copy]
